---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Road test guide — calm confidence on test day";
const description = "A practical, low-stress motorcycle road test guide: checklists, common mistakes, and a simple test-day flow.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/road-test-guide/">
  <section class="card">
    <div class="muted" style="font-weight:900;">Educational content • Canada-wide • Built for anxiety-free prep</div>
    <h1 style="margin:8px 0 0; font-weight:1000;">Road test guide</h1>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; max-width:90ch;">
      This is a <strong>practical checklist</strong> — not a riding lesson. The goal is calm confidence: know what to bring,
      what to check, and how to avoid the classic “I forgot ___” moment.
    </p>

    <div class="card" style="padding:14px; margin-top:12px;">
      <div style="font-weight:1000;">Mentor coordination</div>
      <div class="muted" style="margin-top:6px; max-width:90ch;">
        If you book through the app, use in-app messaging for coordination, clarification, and experience-based safety tips.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-3" style="margin-top:14px; gap:10px;">
      <div class="card" style="padding:14px;">
        <div style="font-weight:1000;">Show up prepared</div>
        <div class="muted" style="margin-top:6px;">Gear + paperwork + a simple plan for the day.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="padding:14px;">
        <div style="font-weight:1000;">Avoid avoidable fails</div>
        <div class="muted" style="margin-top:6px;">Signals, shoulder checks, stops, and lane positioning.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="padding:14px;">
        <div style="font-weight:1000;">Less panic</div>
        <div class="muted" style="margin-top:6px;">A short warm-up routine and a calm “reset” method.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="muted" style="margin-top:12px; font-size:13px;">
      Note: Requirements vary by province/registry. Always follow your registry’s instructions.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <div class="card">
      <h2 style="margin:0 0 10px; font-weight:1000;">Tap-to-expand checklists</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin:0; max-width:92ch;">
        We keep the page scannable. Expand only what you need right now.
      </p>

      <div style="margin-top:12px;">
        <details class="bmb-acc">
          <summary>
            <span>Before you book</span>
           
          </summary>
          <div class="bmb-accBody">
            <div class="muted">Do this before you request a bike/mentor so test day isn’t chaos.</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Confirm your road test time/location</strong> and plan to arrive <strong>30 minutes early</strong> unless your registry tells you otherwise.</li>
              <li><strong>Know the route area</strong>: do a calm drive-through the day before if possible.</li>
              <li><strong>Bring the right documents</strong> (see checklist below).</li>
              <li><strong>Practice the boring stuff</strong>: stops, signals, shoulder checks, lane position.</li>
              <li><strong>Plan your warm-up</strong>: 10 minutes of slow-speed basics before the test.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bmb-acc">
          <summary>
            <span>Gear + documents checklist</span>
           
          </summary>
          <div class="bmb-accBody">
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Helmet</strong> (approved, fits properly, visor/eye protection).</li>
              <li><strong>Jacket</strong> (ideally abrasion-resistant) + <strong>gloves</strong>.</li>
              <li><strong>Long pants</strong> (no shorts) + <strong>over-the-ankle footwear</strong>.</li>
              <li><strong>License</strong> + any registry paperwork / booking confirmation.</li>
              <li><strong>Weather plan</strong>: warm layer, rain layer, and a backup date strategy.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="muted" style="margin-top:10px;">
              Tip: Put everything in one bag the night before. Your brain will thank you.
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bmb-acc">
          <summary>
            <span>Bike sanity checks (quick)</span>
           
          </summary>
          <div class="bmb-accBody">
            <div class="muted">You’re not doing a full inspection — just avoid obvious issues.</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Lights</strong>: headlight / brake light / signals.</li>
              <li><strong>Horn</strong>: works.</li>
              <li><strong>Tires</strong>: visibly okay, no obvious low pressure.</li>
              <li><strong>Mirrors</strong>: positioned for you.</li>
              <li><strong>Controls</strong>: clutch/throttle feel normal; brakes feel firm.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bmb-acc">
          <summary>
            <span>Test-day flow (simple)</span>
            
          </summary>
          <div class="bmb-accBody">
            <ol>
              <li><strong>Arrive early</strong>. Breathe. Don’t rush.
                <div class="muted">Rushing is the #1 way people make dumb mistakes.</div>
              </li>
              <li><strong>Warm up</strong> (10 min): smooth starts/stops, turns, shoulder checks.</li>
              <li><strong>During the test</strong>: scan far ahead, signal early, shoulder check before any move.</li>
              <li><strong>If you make a mistake</strong>: don’t spiral. Fix the next decision.
                <div class="muted">Reset phrase: “Next move only.”</div>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bmb-acc">
          <summary>
            <span>Common mistakes (and how to avoid them)</span>
            
          </summary>
          <div class="bmb-accBody">
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Late signals</strong> → signal earlier than feels necessary.</li>
              <li><strong>No shoulder check</strong> → shoulder check becomes muscle memory: <em>mirror → signal → shoulder check → move</em>.</li>
              <li><strong>Rolling stops</strong> → full stop, visibly.</li>
              <li><strong>Lane position</strong> → be deliberate (don’t drift).
                <div class="muted">Pick a track: left track / center / right track and hold it.</div>
              </li>
              <li><strong>Nerves = stiff controls</strong> → relax grip; smooth throttle.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bmb-acc">
          <summary>
            <span>If the test can’t proceed</span>
            
          </summary>
          <div class="bmb-accBody">
            <div class="muted">Sometimes things happen. The goal is a safe rebook — not a meltdown.</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Unsafe weather</strong>: treat it like a reschedule, not a failure.</li>
              <li><strong>Gear missing</strong>: don’t try to “wing it.” Fix the issue before the next attempt.</li>
              <li><strong>Bike not road-test ready</strong>: stop and reschedule.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="muted" style="margin-top:10px;">
              On <a href="https://borrowmybike.ca" rel="noopener" target="_blank">BorrowMyBike</a>, the app handles the “what happens next” rules (deposits/credits) so both sides are treated fairly.
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bmb-acc">
  <summary>
    <span>Alberta-specific test-day notes</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="bmb-accBody">
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Arrive 30 minutes early</strong> unless your registry gives different instructions.</li>
      <li><strong>Use <a href="https://borrowmybike.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BorrowMyBike.ca</a> to book your road-test motorcycle</strong> and meet your mentor and bike at the registry before the road test.</li>      
      <li><strong>Bring earbuds</strong> for examiner communication.</li>
      <li><strong>If you test on a 3-wheeler</strong>, your Alberta Class 6 will be restricted to 3-wheeled motorcycles.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</details>

<details class="bmb-acc">
  <summary>
    <span>What bikes are not suitable for a Class 6 road test?</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="bmb-accBody">
    <ul>
      <li><strong>50cc and under</strong> should be treated as moped territory, not a full motorcycle road-test bike.</li>
      <li><strong>Automatic motorcycles are allowed</strong> for Alberta Class 6 testing.</li>
      <li><strong>3-wheeled motorcycles are allowed</strong>, but they result in a 3-wheel-only restriction on the licence.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="muted" style="margin-top:10px;">
      Always confirm the exact requirements with your registry if anything about the bike or booking feels unclear.
    </div>
  </div>
</details>
      </div>


      <div class="card" style="padding:14px; margin-top:14px;">
        <div style="font-weight:1000;">Damage &amp; responsibility (quick clarity)</div>
        <div class="muted" style="margin-top:6px; max-width:92ch;">
          Deposits are for accountability and to discourage no-shows — they do not guarantee full damage coverage.
          If something goes wrong on test day, <b>document first</b> and email <b>support@borrowmybike.ca</b> with a short summary and photos. Full details: <a href="https://borrowmybike.ca/legal#damage" rel="noopener" target="_blank" style="font-weight:950; text-decoration: underline;">Damage &amp; responsibility →</a>
          The platform reviews both sides and applies the written rules fairly.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="padding:14px; margin-top:14px;">
        <div style="font-weight:1000;">Want a city-specific version?</div>
        <div class="muted" style="margin-top:6px; max-width:90ch;">
          Pick a city on the home page and we’ll keep “city mode” on — you’ll see local content across pages.
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex; gap:10px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:10px;">
          <a class="cta" href="/">Go pick a city →</a>
          <a class="cta" href="https://borrowmybike.ca" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Open the app →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
